<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-749-470  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 749 470.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Sept 11 1989 v3 n37 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD plans to hire firms to provide weapons data. (Department ofDefense)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Defense (DOD) is working on a proposal that willallow contracted companies to provide technical informationdirectly to weapon systems users instead of having information gothrough distribution centers.andP;  Data management would be a contractline item in DOD contracts.andP;  During the 1990s, with acceptance ofthe Computer-Aided Acquisition and Logistics program, much of theDOD's weapons information will be automated.andP;  The DOD, realizingthat repositories will not be able to handle future electronicsubmissions from vendors, decided it needed to increase itsoptions.andP;  Creating specifications for on-line information wouldsupply such an option.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseData ManagementAutomationOn-LineGovernment ContractsMilitary.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>